1.3. “Source Code” means the preferred form of the Work for making modifications, including without limitation source files, interface definitions, build scripts, configuration files, and other files reasonably necessary to produce a Binary.

1.4. “Binary” means any compiled, assembled, packaged, packaged-for-distribution, linked, or otherwise non-source form of the Work.

1.5. “Modification” means any alteration of the Source Code, and any work based upon, derived from, adapted from, or incorporating the Source Code, in whole or in part, to the extent protected by applicable copyright law.

1.6. “Fork” means any separate development line containing a copy of the Source Code, with or without Modifications.

1.7. “License Change Notice” means a written public notice issued by the Licensor stating that some or all Source Code previously made available under this License shall, from a stated effective date, no longer be licensed under this License and shall instead be subject to a different license or to no public source license.

1.8. “Transition Period” means the twenty-eight (28) calendar day period beginning on the effective date stated in the applicable License Change Notice.

1.9. “Covered Source” means Source Code that is, at the relevant time, both:

(a) distributed or made available under this License; and
(b) owned by the Licensor in whole or in part to the extent necessary for the Licensor to grant, alter, withdraw, replace, or relicense the applicable rights under this License.

For the avoidance of doubt, Covered Source includes only Source Code for which the Licensor has sufficient copyright interest or other written authority to license or relicense under this License.

